# Drift authority map

After a `context-gc` run, this file records one entry per **fact domain** — what the root is, which
derived copies must match it, and how to re-check.

## How to use

- On the next GC run (incremental), read this file first. For each entry, re-check only the
  root→copy pair. Full re-scan only needed if the scope has changed or a new domain was added.
- If a copy is known to intentionally diverge (fork), mark it `FORK` — the GC will skip it.

> Format: one section per fact domain. Authoritative = root. The rest should match.

